and how he's praying for them.

00:17:08.139 --> 00:17:13.619
But as we go to the sixth chapter of the book of Ephesians, and he's nearing the end, he's

00:17:13.619 --> 00:17:17.459
gone through the fact that we're engaged in spiritual warfare, that we need to put on

00:17:17.459 --> 00:17:24.179
the whole armor of God, how important these truths are, that he says in verse number 18,

00:17:24.179 --> 00:17:31.019
praying always with all prayer and supplication in the Spirit, and watching thereunto with

00:17:31.019 --> 00:17:34.459
all perseverance and supplication for all saints.

00:17:34.459 --> 00:17:39.699
Notice the first few words of verse 19, and for me.

00:17:39.699 --> 00:17:42.299
So he tells them, you need to be engaged in prayer.

00:17:42.299 --> 00:17:46.179
And by the way, you're praying not only for all of these saints at the end of verse number

00:17:46.179 --> 00:17:50.719
18, being engaged in intercessory prayer, but then he says, and pray for me.

00:17:50.719 --> 00:17:57.079
Notice what he says, that utterance may be given unto me that I may open my mouth boldly

00:17:57.079 --> 00:18:03.039
to make known the mystery of the gospel, for which I am an ambassador in bonds, that therein

00:18:03.039 --> 00:18:07.079
I may speak boldly as I ought to speak.

00:18:07.079 --> 00:18:12.559
Now when you think about the Apostle Paul, honestly, do you think of an individual that

00:18:12.559 --> 00:18:16.719
would need someone to pray for him to have boldness?

00:18:16.719 --> 00:18:18.299
Honestly.

00:18:18.299 --> 00:18:22.019
If you think about the Apostle Paul, if you've read the New Testament, if you've studied

00:18:22.019 --> 00:18:27.939
the missionary journeys, if you've studied the travels and the ministries of the Apostle

00:18:27.939 --> 00:18:32.899
Paul, you see that he is a man that has great boldness and great courage.

00:18:32.899 --> 00:18:34.479
Would you agree?

00:18:34.479 --> 00:18:39.500
But yet he says to these believers in Ephesus, pray for me that I would have boldness.

00:18:39.500 --> 00:18:40.899
Wow.

00:18:40.899 --> 00:18:45.899
Is that not something that we ought to be asking for people to pray for us to have boldness?

00:18:45.899 --> 00:18:50.899
He says that utterance may be given unto me that I may open my mouth boldly to make

00:18:50.899 --> 00:18:53.179
known the mystery of the gospel.

00:18:53.179 --> 00:18:54.459
Wow.

00:18:54.459 --> 00:18:59.820
We are to have boldness as we go out as the ambassadors, as the representatives of our

00:18:59.820 --> 00:19:02.019
Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.

00:19:02.019 --> 00:19:04.019
And Paul says, here's how I want you to pray for me.

00:19:04.019 --> 00:19:07.139
Pray that I'd have boldness.

00:19:07.139 --> 00:19:11.700
I'd like to think that the believers in Ephesus prayed that way.

00:19:11.700 --> 00:19:12.820
Amen?

00:19:12.820 --> 00:19:18.820
I'd like to think that if I were to send you a letter, if another brother or sister

00:19:18.820 --> 00:19:23.619
were to send you a letter and say, hey, would you pray for me specifically about this thing?

00:19:23.619 --> 00:19:25.579
I'd like to think that you would.

00:19:25.579 --> 00:19:26.579
Amen?

00:19:26.579 --> 00:19:30.859
When missionaries send us update letters, we have the opportunity to hear how things

00:19:30.859 --> 00:19:35.099
are going and how God is working, but then they'll include, would you pray about these

00:19:35.099 --> 00:19:37.059
things specifically?

00:19:37.059 --> 00:19:38.059
So what do we do?

00:19:38.059 --> 00:19:39.579
We engage in prayer.

00:19:39.579 --> 00:19:45.940
We go before the throne of grace on the behalf of others, people that we may never meet until

00:19:45.940 --> 00:19:47.380
glory.

00:19:47.380 --> 00:19:49.579
We pray for them.

00:19:49.579 --> 00:19:54.260
And then the encouragement comes, not only when we're able to send them a note and say,

00:19:54.260 --> 00:19:59.859
I'm praying for you, and they receive encouragement, but the encouragement for us as the one praying

00:19:59.859 --> 00:20:01.940
is when we get the next update letter.

00:20:01.940 --> 00:20:05.740
and read about how so-and-so trusted Christ as their Savior,

00:20:05.740 --> 00:20:08.980
about how so-and-so was invited to a special meeting,

00:20:08.980 --> 00:20:13.900
and we begin to see how God answers prayer.

00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:16.500
That's encouraging for us as the people of God.

00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:17.900
Notice in the book of Colossians,

00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:20.020
the passage in which we've dealt with here

00:20:20.020 --> 00:20:22.380
is our springboard in verse number three of chapter one,

00:20:22.380 --> 00:20:23.700
praying always for you.

00:20:23.700 --> 00:20:26.260
But notice in Colossians chapter number four,

00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:30.260
the Apostle Paul tells these believers in Colossae

00:20:30.260 --> 00:20:32.740
in verse number two, continue in prayer

00:20:32.740 --> 00:20:35.060
and watch in the same with thanksgiving.

00:20:35.060 --> 00:20:37.180
Notice verse number three, with all,

00:20:37.180 --> 00:20:41.460
praying also for us that God would open unto us

00:20:41.460 --> 00:20:44.020
a door of utterance to speak the mystery of Christ

00:20:44.020 --> 00:20:46.380
for which I am also in bonds

00:20:46.380 --> 00:20:51.100
that I may make it manifest as I ought to speak.

00:20:51.100 --> 00:20:52.540
Paul tells them in the beginning of the book,

00:20:52.540 --> 00:20:54.220
I'm praying always for you.

00:20:55.140 --> 00:20:57.140
Now would you pray for me?

00:20:57.140 --> 00:20:59.540
And here's how I'd ask that you'd pray for me.

00:21:00.700 --> 00:21:03.980
The example in the word of God of intercessory prayer.

00:21:03.980 --> 00:21:06.380
Paul says it this way in first Thessalonians five

00:21:06.380 --> 00:21:11.060
in verse 25, very simply, brethren, pray for us.

00:21:11.060 --> 00:21:12.260
Pray for us.

00:21:12.260 --> 00:21:14.940
He says it again in second Thessalonians chapter number three

00:21:14.940 --> 00:21:16.060
in verse number one, he says,

00:21:16.060 --> 00:21:18.779
finally, brethren, pray for us.

00:21:19.660 --> 00:21:22.620
And we begin to understand and look to the word of God

00:21:22.620 --> 00:21:25.900
and see the example of intercessory prayer.

00:21:25.900 --> 00:21:28.100
We see it all throughout the New Testament.

00:21:28.100 --> 00:21:33.100
We see these believers, these that have gone before us

00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:36.260
that have understood the importance,

00:21:36.260 --> 00:21:39.020
the significance of intercessory prayer,

00:21:39.020 --> 00:21:42.700
the privilege of going to the throne room of heaven

00:21:42.700 --> 00:21:45.380
on the behalf of others.

00:21:45.380 --> 00:21:47.700
And not only does Paul share with us

00:21:47.700 --> 00:21:49.740
that I'm praying for you,

00:21:49.740 --> 00:21:51.260
and here's how I'm praying for you

00:21:51.260 --> 00:21:53.819
as we read the Scriptures and the individual recipients,

00:21:53.819 --> 00:21:56.720
but we find that Paul then says, would you pray for me?

00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.920
You know, it's a great thing to look to God

00:22:00.920 --> 00:22:03.840
and to understand that God is a God

00:22:03.840 --> 00:22:05.720
who hears and answers prayer.

00:22:07.279 --> 00:22:10.760
When I say to you, when you say to me, I'm praying for you.

00:22:12.040 --> 00:22:13.240
What does it do for you?

00:22:14.080 --> 00:22:15.440
I hope it encourages you.

00:22:16.600 --> 00:22:19.839
And here's the reality, as fellow believers,

00:22:19.839 --> 00:22:22.520
as Bible-believing Christians,

00:22:22.520 --> 00:22:24.960
if brother Tony comes to me,

00:22:24.960 --> 00:22:26.880
and I've known brother Tony for a long time,

00:22:26.880 --> 00:22:30.000
and I understand that he's saved, that he's trusted Christ,

00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:33.720
he's serving the same God and the God of the universe,

00:22:33.720 --> 00:22:36.760
and he says to me, pastor, I'm praying for you.

00:22:36.760 --> 00:22:37.919
You know what I understand about that?

00:22:37.919 --> 00:22:42.520
I understand that Tony is going to the God of the universe,

00:22:42.520 --> 00:22:45.360
the sovereign God on my behalf,

00:22:45.360 --> 00:22:46.960
the God who is able to do exceeding,

00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:49.639
abundantly above all that we ask or think.

00:22:49.639 --> 00:22:52.300
Can I tell you how much different that is

00:22:52.300 --> 00:22:55.580
than just somebody in the world that says,

00:22:55.580 --> 00:22:56.699
actually, they've changed it.

00:22:56.699 --> 00:22:58.900
Now they like to say, I'm thinking about you.

00:22:59.860 --> 00:23:00.979
Am I right?

00:23:02.059 --> 00:23:03.059
Seriously.

00:23:03.059 --> 00:23:05.220
It used to be that they'd say, I'm praying for you.

00:23:05.220 --> 00:23:07.020
Who are you praying to?

00:23:07.020 --> 00:23:09.260
You don't believe in the same God that I believe in.

00:23:09.260 --> 00:23:11.860
You're not serving the same God that I serve.

00:23:11.860 --> 00:23:13.500
So who exactly are you praying?

00:23:13.500 --> 00:23:14.779
Do you understand what I'm saying?

00:23:14.779 --> 00:23:17.100
And so I'm not seeking, through this message,

00:23:17.100 --> 00:23:18.779
to criticize those individuals.

00:23:18.779 --> 00:23:20.100
That's not the point of my message.

00:23:20.100 --> 00:23:22.540
That's not the point of the subject matter.

00:23:22.540 --> 00:23:25.339
But what I want to encourage you with this morning

00:23:26.260 --> 00:23:28.740
is that as fellow believers,

00:23:28.740 --> 00:23:31.020
when we say that we're praying one for another,

00:23:31.020 --> 00:23:34.860
when you communicate to me or I communicate to you

00:23:34.860 --> 00:23:37.100
that I'm praying for you, that we serve the same God

00:23:37.100 --> 00:23:38.820
and He is Jehovah God.

00:23:38.820 --> 00:23:40.979
He is Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the end,

00:23:40.979 --> 00:23:42.460
the first and the last.

00:23:42.460 --> 00:23:45.580
He is the omnipotent God who reigns,

00:23:45.580 --> 00:23:49.419
who's able to do exceeding, abundantly above

00:23:49.419 --> 00:23:51.100
all that we ask or think.

00:23:51.100 --> 00:23:53.740
With Him, nothing is impossible.

00:23:53.740 --> 00:23:56.699
You understand the significance of the statement

00:23:56.699 --> 00:23:58.339
when someone would say to you,

00:23:58.339 --> 00:23:59.900
when you would say to someone,

00:23:59.900 --> 00:24:01.860
I'm praying for you.

00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.220
It's powerful.

00:24:05.979 --> 00:24:08.540
It's a privilege that is ours.

00:24:10.779 --> 00:24:15.139
I don't say to Armando and Deanna on Friday

00:24:15.139 --> 00:24:17.860
when Camila was going to have her procedure,

00:24:17.860 --> 00:24:20.019
I didn't just say, I'm thinking about you.

00:24:22.540 --> 00:24:23.980
That's not what I texted you, is it?

00:24:23.980 --> 00:24:26.220
Armando's not here this morning, he's home with Camila,

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:28.100
but that's not what I texted Armando.

00:24:29.220 --> 00:24:31.820
Maria, when Manuel was going into surgery,

00:24:31.820 --> 00:24:33.540
did I say I'm thinking about you?

00:24:33.540 --> 00:24:34.380
No.

00:24:35.660 --> 00:24:37.459
I'm praying.

00:24:37.459 --> 00:24:40.500
Oftentimes, if you, I'd let you look at my text messages,

00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:41.700
I don't have anything to hide,

00:24:41.700 --> 00:24:45.420
but I sent text messages to pastor friends this morning.

00:24:46.420 --> 00:24:49.019
And I didn't just say, I'm thinking about you.

00:24:49.019 --> 00:24:50.260
I said, I'm praying for you,

00:24:50.260 --> 00:24:52.380
and here's how I'm praying for you.

00:24:52.380 --> 00:24:54.260
I'm praying that God would give you boldness

00:24:54.260 --> 00:24:56.299
as you stand behind the sacred desk.

00:24:56.299 --> 00:24:58.260
I'm praying that the people of God

00:24:58.260 --> 00:25:00.820
would be attentive to the preaching of the Word of God,

00:25:00.820 --> 00:25:02.299
that decisions would be made

00:25:02.299 --> 00:25:05.260
that would glorify God Almighty.

00:25:05.260 --> 00:25:07.059
That's how we pray one for another.

00:25:07.940 --> 00:25:12.940
And listen, as a receiver, it encourages me.

00:25:13.940 --> 00:25:17.899
As the one praying, it encourages me

00:25:17.899 --> 00:25:22.899
when I get to hear how God worked and what God did.

00:25:23.100 --> 00:25:24.899
We serve an awesome God.

00:25:26.540 --> 00:25:28.580
And prayer is not designed

00:25:28.580 --> 00:25:32.179
to just be a grocery list of my needs.

00:25:33.820 --> 00:25:34.860
Amen?

00:25:34.860 --> 00:25:36.019
It really isn't.

00:25:38.459 --> 00:25:42.500
This aspect of intercessory prayer is biblical.

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:46.019
In fact, as I look to the Word of God,

00:25:46.019 --> 00:25:48.779
I see more examples of intercessory prayer

00:25:48.779 --> 00:25:50.420
than I do of personal prayer.

00:25:54.820 --> 00:25:56.700
Not only do we see the example,

00:25:56.700 --> 00:25:58.980
say it's great, we got some Bible truth.

00:25:58.980 --> 00:26:00.220
How does it apply?

00:26:00.220 --> 00:26:01.059
I would say this,

00:26:01.059 --> 00:26:02.540
if I were giving you points this morning,

00:26:02.540 --> 00:26:07.540
number two, purpose to engage in intercessory prayer.

00:26:07.660 --> 00:26:09.619
Intercessory prayer.

00:26:09.619 --> 00:26:13.299
Not only do we consider the example of intercessory prayer,

00:26:13.299 --> 00:26:15.459
but when we see that example,

00:26:15.459 --> 00:26:18.619
then we ought to purpose in our lives

00:26:18.619 --> 00:26:22.580
to engage in intercessory prayer.

00:26:22.580 --> 00:26:23.820
Now let me say this,

00:26:24.820 --> 00:26:27.260
if you have not engaged in intercessory prayer,

00:26:27.260 --> 00:26:29.299
if it's a new subject matter to you,

00:26:29.299 --> 00:26:30.480
and you've not heard of this,

00:26:30.480 --> 00:26:32.700
you've not been thoughtful of this truth,

00:26:32.700 --> 00:26:35.860
then I would not expect you to be praying always,

00:26:35.860 --> 00:26:36.700
night and day,

00:26:36.700 --> 00:26:38.080
and all of these things that we see

00:26:38.080 --> 00:26:39.619
in the life of the Apostle Paul,

00:26:39.619 --> 00:26:41.899
but I would expect that you would purpose to engage

00:26:41.899 --> 00:26:44.360
in that you would start somewhere

00:26:44.360 --> 00:26:46.260
on engaging in intercessory prayer.

00:26:46.260 --> 00:26:47.380
Here's the reality,

00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:50.459
if I'm going to engage in intercessory prayer,

00:26:50.459 --> 00:26:53.580
I need to have some knowledge and some information

00:26:53.580 --> 00:26:54.720
in order to do so.

00:26:56.179 --> 00:26:57.860
I'm not suggesting this morning

00:26:57.860 --> 00:26:59.860
that we want to know every detail

00:26:59.860 --> 00:27:02.100
about one another's lives and so on and so forth,

00:27:02.100 --> 00:27:03.739
but there's some specific things

00:27:04.019 --> 00:27:06.540
that if I'm going to engage in intercessory prayer,

00:27:06.540 --> 00:27:07.739
it's good for me to know,

00:27:07.739 --> 00:27:11.059
to have the knowledge so that I can pray specifically.

00:27:11.059 --> 00:27:12.500
There have been times in which,

00:27:12.500 --> 00:27:14.339
I'll use Brother Mark as an example,

00:27:14.339 --> 00:27:16.940
he's had some test or some things coming up,

00:27:16.940 --> 00:27:17.940
and I knew about it,

00:27:17.940 --> 00:27:19.580
he communicated it to me, why?

00:27:19.580 --> 00:27:21.080
So I could pray for him.

00:27:22.459 --> 00:27:24.459
Someone has a medical test that's coming up,

00:27:24.459 --> 00:27:26.739
someone has an interview,

00:27:26.739 --> 00:27:29.220
somebody has an opportunity

00:27:29.220 --> 00:27:31.860
to share the gospel with someone,

00:27:31.899 --> 00:27:34.380
we're able to pray specifically.

00:27:34.380 --> 00:27:36.860
Ms. Joyce called Holly a couple of weeks ago,

00:27:36.860 --> 00:27:38.420
I don't remember the exact date,

00:27:38.420 --> 00:27:40.299
but Ms. Joyce called Holly and said,

00:27:40.299 --> 00:27:42.380
Holly, I'd like to ask if you and your family

00:27:42.380 --> 00:27:45.019
could pray for Wally, Joyce's son Wally.

00:27:46.179 --> 00:27:48.100
And she says this on the phone to Holly,

00:27:48.100 --> 00:27:49.660
I did not speak to Ms. Joyce,

00:27:49.660 --> 00:27:51.059
she spoke to Wally.

00:27:51.059 --> 00:27:53.899
And she said, Wally met somebody this morning

00:27:53.899 --> 00:27:56.459
and was able to give a gospel tract to him

00:27:56.459 --> 00:27:57.779
is my understanding,

00:27:57.779 --> 00:27:59.940
and they were able to speak about the gospel

00:27:59.940 --> 00:28:01.260
for just a moment,

00:28:01.260 --> 00:28:05.260
and Wally invited him to have dinner at five o'clock

00:28:05.260 --> 00:28:07.339
and they have a meeting scheduled,

00:28:07.339 --> 00:28:09.220
and Wally's whole purpose

00:28:09.220 --> 00:28:11.100
is to give that man the gospel,

00:28:11.100 --> 00:28:12.860
would you pray?

00:28:12.860 --> 00:28:14.279
You know what we did?

00:28:14.279 --> 00:28:16.200
I'm not patting myself on the back,

00:28:16.200 --> 00:28:17.459
but you know what we did?

00:28:17.459 --> 00:28:19.019
At 4.57,

00:28:20.019 --> 00:28:22.640
we stopped as a family,

00:28:22.640 --> 00:28:23.480
and we prayed.

00:28:24.519 --> 00:28:25.959
We prayed.

00:28:25.959 --> 00:28:28.619
We said, God, you're the God of the universe.

00:28:29.619 --> 00:28:31.940
And this appointment is scheduled,

00:28:31.940 --> 00:28:35.340
and Wally purposes to share the gospel,

00:28:35.340 --> 00:28:37.119
would you soften the heart of this man?

00:28:37.119 --> 00:28:38.940
Would you help him to understand?

